  <!-- Section: FAQ -->
  <section id="faq" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How does the 50% tax reduction work?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          If you become a Greek tax resident on the DN visa, you can claim 50% reduction on foreign-source income for up to 7 years. You'll pay Greek tax rates on the remaining 50%. Consult a Greek tax advisor to set this up properly.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I renew the visa?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes. The initial 1-year visa can be renewed for 2 additional years, giving you up to 3 years total. Renewal requires continuing to meet income and insurance requirements.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I travel in Schengen?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes. Greece is a Schengen member. Your DN visa allows travel throughout the 27-country Schengen zone.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is island life practical for remote work?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Depends on the island. Crete, Rhodes, and Corfu have good infrastructure. Smaller Cycladic islands (Mykonos, Santorini) are seasonal and can have internet issues. Test before committing.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need to speak Greek?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          No, especially in Athens and tourist areas. However, Greek bureaucracy often functions in Greek, so having local help or a translator for official matters is useful.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about the nomad community?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Growing but smaller than Portugal or Bali. Athens has several coworking spaces and nomad meetups. Islands have seasonal nomad gatherings in summer.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

